## Phase 2: Physics + Character Controller

### Deliverables
Raccoon has gravity, lands on ground, jumps with space, runs left/right. Uses avian2d + bevy-tnua. One-way platforms work. Jump buffer + coyote time. Replaces Phase 1 temp input.

### New Files
```
src/physics/mod.rs            — Avian2dPlugin, gravity config
src/physics/config.rs         — PhysicsConfig (gravity, speeds, jump height)
src/player/controller.rs      — TnuaController + TnuaAvian2dSensorShape setup
src/player/input.rs           — Reads keyboard, feeds TnuaBuiltinWalk/Jump actions
src/level/mod.rs              — Level module
src/level/components.rs       — TileEntity, LayerTransition, etc.
src/level/test_level.rs       — Hardcoded test level: ground + platforms at reachable heights
```

### Key Details
- avian2d `RigidBody::Dynamic` on player, `RigidBody::Static` on ground
- avian2d `Collider::rectangle()` for AABB collision
- TnuaBuiltinWalk: speed 200, TnuaBuiltinJump: height ~5 tiles (160 units)
- Jump buffer: 150ms timer. Coyote time: 100ms after leaving ground.
- Collision layers: Player, Ground, Platform, Enemy

### Agent Focus
- **Spec**: Define collider sizes, Tnua walk/jump params, one-way platform layer masks
- **Implementation**: Integrate avian2d + tnua, set up collision layers, wire input
- **Test**: Test jump height reaches target, test one-way platform passthrough, test no ground clipping
- **Critic**: Check for physics jitter, verify FixedUpdate vs Update scheduling

### Verification
- Player falls, lands, no jitter or sinking
- Jump reaches ~5 tile heights consistently
- One-way platforms: pass through from below, land on top
- `cargo test` — physics config, controller setup

---

## Phase 3: Tilemap + Level Loading + Camera

### Deliverables
Complete Forest level (3 layers) with Kenney tiles. Auto-tiling for ground edges. Camera follows player with clamping. Layer switching via E key. Parallax background at Z-depth.

### New Files
```
src/tilemap/mod.rs            — TilemapPlugin
src/tilemap/tilemap.rs        — TileMap struct, TileType enum, grid_to_world
src/tilemap/autotile.rs       — Neighbor-based atlas index selection (16 edge/corner variants)
src/tilemap/spawn.rs          — Spawn Mesh3d quads with avian2d colliders per tile
src/level/level_data.rs       — LevelId, Layer, LevelData structs
src/level/forest.rs           — Forest 3 layers (validated: all platforms ≤5 rows apart)
src/level/systems.rs          — load_level, switch_layer, camera_follow
src/rendering/parallax.rs     — Background quads at Z=-20 to Z=-100
```

### Key Details
- Auto-tiling: Solid tiles check 8 neighbors → select from ~16 atlas variants
- Camera lerp speed 5.0, clamp to world bounds
- Layer switch: despawn TileEntity, spawn new layer, teleport player to matching transition
- Parallax: Kenney PNGs on Mesh3d quads at negative Z depths

### Agent Focus
- **Spec**: Define tilemap format, tile-to-atlas-index mapping for auto-tiling, camera clamping math
- **Implementation**: Build tilemap renderer with Mesh3d quads + atlas UVs, connect avian2d colliders
- **Test**: Test tilemap bounds, auto-tile edge cases, layer transition player placement
- **Critic**: Verify no gaps between tiles, confirm Z-ordering, check entity cleanup on layer switch

### Verification
- Forest renders with proper edge tiles
- Camera never shows void outside bounds
- Layer switch places player on solid ground
- Parallax creates depth effect
- `cargo test` — tilemap indexing, auto-tile, grid_to_world

