## Phase 6: HUD + Dialogue + Save/Load

### Deliverables
Health bar + collectible counter HUD. NPC dialogue. Save/load 3 slots. Pause menu. Main menu.

### Key Details
- HUD: Bevy UI nodes (separate from Camera3d). Hearts + counter.
- Dialogue: lines array, advance with Space/E, locks player movement
- Save: JSON via `dirs` crate. Stores level, layer, position, health, collected, puzzles.
- Menu: TitleScreen → MainMenu → Playing (with Paused overlay)

---

## Phase 7: Audio + Animation + Particles

### Deliverables
Background music per level. SFX for all events. Raccoon walk/idle/jump animation. Enemy animation. Particle bursts.

### Key Details
- Music: Kenney Music Loops (Farm Frolics, Mischief Stroll, Mission Plausible, Night at the Beach)
- SFX: Kenney Retro Sounds (jump, pickup, creature/damage, lose/death)
- Animation: UV cycling on Mesh3d StandardMaterial
- Particles: lightweight Mesh3d quads with lifetime + velocity + fade

---

## Phase 8: Polish + 3D Lighting + Visual Effects

### Deliverables
Per-level lighting themes. Point lights in underground. Weather particles. Vignette. Level name flash. Transition fades.

### Key Details
- DirectionalLight3d color/angle per level (warm Forest, cool City, golden Sanctuary)
- PointLight3d at specific positions (torches underground, street lamps)
- AmbientLight varies per layer (dark underground, bright rooftop)
- Weather: rain in City, leaves in Forest, dust in Sanctuary

